WEBVTT

03:27.807 --> 03:29.035
Benjamin.

03:33.980 --> 03:36.949
Benjamin. Angelo's brother.
I sent a telegram.

03:41.921 --> 03:45.357
I am Miranda, your sister in law.
Well, sort of.

03:52.332 --> 03:54.857
I never had a sister in law before.

03:54.968 --> 03:56.196
Lucky me!

03:58.004 --> 04:00.097
What should I call you? Benjamin?

04:00.206 --> 04:01.730
Bennie's good.

04:03.610 --> 04:05.407
Are you in the Navy, Bennie?

04:06.346 --> 04:10.783
No, I work on a cruise ship, <i>Infinity Lines,</i>

04:10.883 --> 04:13.078
I'm a waiter, sort of.

04:14.854 --> 04:17.516
You are so much younger than I thought.

04:19.726 --> 04:21.488
I'm going to be 18 on Sunday.

04:22.262 --> 04:25.891
In three days! I'll throw a party.

04:26.299 --> 04:27.425
Great.

04:29.669 --> 04:31.637
Let me see if he's awake.

04:31.738 --> 04:36.334
Because he has a hard time
falling asleep, you know.

04:48.888 --> 04:50.116
Tetro.

04:50.890 --> 04:53.381
Are you awake? Your brother's here.

05:05.505 --> 05:09.305
I was just a little kid
when he went on his writing sabbatical.

05:11.744 --> 05:12.904
That...

05:13.313 --> 05:15.577
That's the last time I saw him.

05:17.350 --> 05:21.753
I'm so happy to see you, Bennie,
and meet you and all, but...

05:26.926 --> 05:30.089
He really doesn't want
to know his family anymore.

05:36.269 --> 05:37.998
I guess he's up now.

05:39.839 --> 05:40.806
No.

05:41.641 --> 05:43.438
He wants me to go in.

05:48.181 --> 05:50.411
But you can stay here tonight.

06:02.895 --> 06:04.192
Thank you.

06:06.199 --> 06:08.133
You know, he's really...

06:11.738 --> 06:14.673
I don't want you to have your feelings hurt.

09:43.683 --> 09:44.809
Jesus.

09:52.124 --> 09:54.319
What the fuck happened to you?

09:56.662 --> 09:58.425
I walked into a bus.

10:02.168 --> 10:03.999
Did she get you coffee?

10:05.271 --> 10:06.863
No, I just woke up.

10:07.573 --> 10:09.803
She's been really nice.

10:11.043 --> 10:15.377
I hate nice, especially the word.
I hate the word "nice."

10:17.149 --> 10:18.343
Oh, man.

10:22.121 --> 10:23.588
Are you okay?

10:24.023 --> 10:25.854
What happened, Bennie?

10:27.393 --> 10:29.884
You get in a fight with the Great One?

10:30.863 --> 10:33.195
I ran away from military school.

10:33.966 --> 10:36.366
Escaped from prison, more like it.

10:37.703 --> 10:39.330
Tell me about it.

10:42.508 --> 10:45.477
Dad doesn't know where I am.

10:47.580 --> 10:50.845
I got this job because
I knew how to wear a uniform.

10:52.084 --> 10:53.745
Lied about my age.

10:55.588 --> 10:58.455
You just took off?
Yeah.

11:00.393 --> 11:01.860
Just like you.

11:07.299 --> 11:09.665
Come on, baby.
Morning.

11:15.608 --> 11:18.600
Look how beautiful my baby is.

11:19.578 --> 11:21.205
Look at that face.

11:22.415 --> 11:25.612
Doesn't she look like Ava Gardner
with her hair like that?

11:25.718 --> 11:27.345
Who's Ava Gardner?

11:32.892 --> 11:35.656
I was surprised to hear from you, Bennie.

11:36.562 --> 11:39.827
Well, I...
My boat had an engine malfunction.

11:42.868 --> 11:46.235
It's gonna take about
four or five days to fix it.

11:46.872 --> 11:49.033
So, you're working on a ship?

11:49.475 --> 11:53.502
Well, I'm just...
I'm a waiter, but I caught the travel bug.

11:54.580 --> 11:55.842
From you.

11:56.482 --> 11:57.710
From me?

11:58.517 --> 12:01.782
Well, then let's hope
that's all you caught, Bennie.

12:02.488 --> 12:04.752
You remember when you moved in the attic

12:04.857 --> 12:08.122
and you had all those, like, maps?

12:08.227 --> 12:12.664
Remember that, with the Tahiti,
and the Pacific, Pitcairn Island?

12:13.466 --> 12:17.300
So, they're fixing the engine
on the boat, right?

12:19.004 --> 12:22.235
Yeah.
So, you can still sleep on the boat?

12:22.341 --> 12:24.275
He can stay with us.

12:24.910 --> 12:26.434
Why not, Tetro?

12:26.846 --> 12:28.575
It's only one week.

12:29.181 --> 12:31.581
Let's go out and show him La Boca.

12:34.587 --> 12:36.612
Okay. Let's go for a walk.

12:37.223 --> 12:39.691
Go ahead, put your pants on.
Okay.

12:45.364 --> 12:48.663
Little Bennie, the able bodied seaman.

12:50.936 --> 12:54.394
I'm not even a waiter, not even.

12:55.107 --> 12:56.802
I'll jump in the shower
and be ready in 10 minutes.

12:56.909 --> 12:58.206
Miranda.

12:59.145 --> 13:01.170
Just me and him, okay?

13:36.615 --> 13:39.846
Listen, you stay one week, okay?

13:40.252 --> 13:43.517
That boat sails, you're on it.
Sure. Thanks, Angie.

13:45.057 --> 13:47.685
Angie's dead. My name is Tetro.

14:17.022 --> 14:18.250
Sit here.

14:43.515 --> 14:46.916
How come you say I'm your friend
and not your brother?

14:47.253 --> 14:49.016
Do you speak Spanish?

14:49.355 --> 14:51.380
Enough to understand that.

14:53.058 --> 14:55.925
People around here
don't know much about me.

14:56.295 --> 14:59.753
Miranda doesn't even know
who our father is.

15:00.599 --> 15:02.794
I'd like to keep it that way.

15:04.436 --> 15:06.131
I don't care. Yeah.

15:09.074 --> 15:10.041
What?

15:10.142 --> 15:14.476
It's just, it's gonna be kind of hard to have
a conversation if I can't ask any questions.

15:14.580 --> 15:16.571
And who wants a conversation?

15:17.583 --> 15:18.743
Not me.

15:44.476 --> 15:46.876
So, why did you come here, Bennie?

15:53.252 --> 15:55.117
I don't like questions.

15:55.554 --> 15:56.521
Hey.

15:57.923 --> 16:02.053
Don't do me, do you. I'll do me. Okay?

16:02.161 --> 16:04.129
It's just, it's not fair.

16:05.331 --> 16:10.394
You left, you never came back and got me,
and I didn't even get, like, an explanation.

16:11.637 --> 16:13.468
And you're my brother?

16:28.554 --> 16:30.579
The ship sails on Tuesday at 2:00 p.m.
Okay.

16:30.689 --> 16:32.281
Don't forget to call in.

16:39.365 --> 16:41.230
Hi, Bennie.
Hi, Anita.

16:42.935 --> 16:45.733
So, he survived four bad accidents.

16:45.838 --> 16:51.276
And one more, with his mother, before that.

16:54.146 --> 16:56.944
Well, you know we have different mothers?

16:57.049 --> 16:59.176
His died in a car accident.

17:02.287 --> 17:05.381
Yes, but...

17:06.157 --> 17:08.148
Tell me about your mother.

17:09.161 --> 17:10.788
About mine?
Yes.

17:12.131 --> 17:14.998
She's been in a coma for nine years.

17:21.173 --> 17:24.142
We're going to have
some good times this week.

17:26.211 --> 17:32.150
A family needs as much fun as it can get,
don't you think?

17:53.372 --> 17:55.704
Ana, no! No!

18:04.883 --> 18:07.408
Actually, they're very much in love.

18:07.953 --> 18:09.318
That's love?

18:10.689 --> 18:12.987
Did you ever sleep with a girl?

18:14.126 --> 18:15.218
What?

18:15.828 --> 18:16.817
No.

19:10.382 --> 19:14.443
That's Abelardo Vaca Castex, some phony.

19:46.618 --> 19:47.778
<i>"Fausta,</i>

19:50.055 --> 19:51.750
"A drama in verse."

19:54.693 --> 19:56.422
What could be worse?

20:10.709 --> 20:12.438
Do you like dancing?

20:53.518 --> 20:57.978
Well, Bennie, what would you like
for your birthday? Tell me.

20:59.191 --> 21:03.594
Just this, to be here
with you and Tetro, here, and...

21:05.530 --> 21:07.760
You know, Tetro's...

21:07.866 --> 21:11.029
I don't remember. How do you say this?

21:12.170 --> 21:13.228
Cast.

21:13.538 --> 21:15.904
Tetro's cast is coming off today.

21:16.575 --> 21:19.066
I bet he'll be back to his old self.

21:20.512 --> 21:21.945
I can't wait.

21:22.848 --> 21:24.475
What's that like?

21:25.484 --> 21:27.145
You can't imagine.

21:27.619 --> 21:31.077
Full of interesting things, you know,
brilliant things.

21:32.658 --> 21:36.719
Also, he has a warm heart, you know?

21:38.063 --> 21:43.365
Well, more of a warm heart
than he's had lately, of course.

21:44.770 --> 21:46.328
Are you married?

21:48.106 --> 21:49.573
As if I were.

21:58.050 --> 22:02.987
The doctor said that I could walk
without my cane if I'm very careful. So...

22:06.491 --> 22:08.925
Easy.
No problem.

22:12.331 --> 22:13.491
My leg!
Are you okay?

22:16.468 --> 22:17.958
Miranda's kiss.

22:19.037 --> 22:21.938
Miranda's kiss! The miracle cure!

22:22.240 --> 22:24.105
She fixed me right up.

22:24.343 --> 22:26.402
One kiss, and it's perfect!

22:29.915 --> 22:31.348
You fixed me.

22:35.087 --> 22:38.955
What were you doing?
You dancing for Bennie?

22:40.292 --> 22:42.123
Just doing my workout.

22:44.596 --> 22:46.223
Dressed like that?

22:47.466 --> 22:49.593
As always.
Your workout?

22:49.701 --> 22:50.895
Asshole!

22:51.937 --> 22:52.926
Okay.

23:17.028 --> 23:20.759
So, you call him your brother
and me your friend?

23:20.866 --> 23:22.299
What is that?

23:23.335 --> 23:25.701
Would you like to go back
to the boat, Bennie?

23:25.804 --> 23:27.669
Sleep on your hammock?

23:28.540 --> 23:31.566
You couldn't just say it? "Brother"?

23:33.412 --> 23:35.573
Brother. Okay?

23:37.916 --> 23:38.883
Yeah, thanks.

23:48.126 --> 23:50.094
Happy I have my cast off.

23:52.664 --> 23:55.132
Maybe you'll start your work again?

23:57.502 --> 23:58.730
My work?

24:00.572 --> 24:02.005
Your writing?

24:02.541 --> 24:04.270
I don't have a pencil.
Well, you went on this...

24:04.376 --> 24:06.207
I don't have a pencil.

24:11.116 --> 24:12.743
I'm a writer, too.

24:13.418 --> 24:15.352
What do you write about?

24:16.888 --> 24:18.856
I walked away from that.

24:20.792 --> 24:24.455
How do you walk away from your work?
Doesn't it follow you?

24:27.532 --> 24:29.397
So, what was it about?

24:45.817 --> 24:47.648
It was about brothers.

24:49.287 --> 24:50.686
Yeah, and...

24:52.390 --> 24:56.952
One brother, a prodigy in music,

24:57.062 --> 24:59.963
and the older brother,
also a great musician.

25:01.299 --> 25:02.926
The theme is ancient.

25:05.871 --> 25:07.065
Rivalry.

25:08.139 --> 25:10.835
You're writing the story of our father?

25:15.881 --> 25:19.282
One brother goes to New York City,
becomes a big star,

25:19.384 --> 25:24.083
he does nothing to help the older brother,
who taught him everything he knew.

25:24.589 --> 25:27.057
Uncle Alfie? The Tootsie Rolls?

25:28.326 --> 25:29.691
Uncle Alfie.

25:33.231 --> 25:34.858
Yeah, Uncle Alfie.

25:37.936 --> 25:40.029
You know what?
I'm breaking my own rules here.

25:40.138 --> 25:41.469
What rules?

25:42.407 --> 25:43.806
What about your mother?

25:43.909 --> 25:46.605
She was, like, this famous singer,
I know, and she died,

25:46.711 --> 25:49.612
but no one's ever told me
anything about her.

25:50.782 --> 25:54.309
Bennie, I thought we had an agreement.
What agreement?

25:56.087 --> 25:57.748
What about my mom?

26:08.667 --> 26:14.071
Listen, I divorced myself
from my family, okay?

26:15.006 --> 26:19.943
Father, sisters, all of it. All of it. All right?

26:20.612 --> 26:23.740
I don't want to talk about it. That's it.

26:25.850 --> 26:27.579
Don't you love them?

26:29.287 --> 26:30.914
Yeah, I love them.

26:32.624 --> 26:35.058
You know what love is
in a family like ours, Bennie?

26:35.160 --> 26:37.424
It's a quick stab in the heart.

26:39.664 --> 26:42.258
I knew your mother died in a car accident,

26:42.367 --> 26:45.427
I just never knew
that you were driving the car.

26:53.545 --> 26:55.274
Well, now you know.

26:58.950 --> 27:01.885
She didn't tell me, Tetro.
Wait, she didn't tell me.

27:01.987 --> 27:05.514
Thanks a lot, Miranda.
She didn't tell me, Tetro!

27:06.925 --> 27:08.392
She didn't...

27:12.263 --> 27:16.597
Tetro, Miranda didn't tell me anything!
I figured it out by myself.

27:28.380 --> 27:30.473
I only have a few days more.

27:31.583 --> 27:34.381
Maybe I should just move back on the boat.

27:36.621 --> 27:38.213
What is with him?

27:45.130 --> 27:50.625
He's like a genius, but without
enough accomplishments, you know?

27:52.170 --> 27:55.571
That's why his behavior is like this.

27:56.007 --> 28:00.068
One day, it's...
Another day, he's completely an asshole.

28:01.279 --> 28:03.213
You sound like a doctor.

28:03.715 --> 28:05.205
I am a doctor.

28:06.351 --> 28:09.343
When I met him,
I was his doctor at the asylum.

28:09.821 --> 28:12.153
Asylum? What kind of asylum?

28:14.459 --> 28:16.450
It was called La Colifata.

28:25.036 --> 28:28.301
<i>With the radio for an hour a week,</i>
<i>on Saturdays,</i>

28:41.753 --> 28:47.692
<i>I came from Europe to Argentina</i>
<i>to study with the founder of La Colifata,</i>

28:48.927 --> 28:53.091
<i>who realized that</i>
<i>whoever had the microphone</i>

28:53.198 --> 28:55.894
<i>flnally had found someone to listen,</i>

30:03.568 --> 30:05.502
<i>He said he was a writer,</i>

30:07.005 --> 30:11.237
<i>and he held everything he had written</i>
<i>against his breast,</i>

30:12.877 --> 30:15.277
<i>It was the only copy that existed,</i>

30:18.583 --> 30:20.517
That is where I met him.

30:22.821 --> 30:25.187
Then finally, he said...

31:43.234 --> 31:44.633
My father is

31:52.477 --> 31:54.342
a real son of a bitch.

31:55.747 --> 31:59.274
My father could be really mean
and really violent.

32:00.919 --> 32:02.784
And he could hit hard.

32:15.533 --> 32:19.128
Then I did... I did the unforgivable.

32:21.372 --> 32:24.102
Crazier than my craziest patient.

32:29.447 --> 32:31.381
<i>I fell in love with him,</i>

36:09.367 --> 36:11.335
<i>He was the older brother,</i>

36:12.270 --> 36:16.104
<i>But Alfredo, dear, sweet Uncle Alfle</i>

36:17.175 --> 36:19.666
<i>was summoned downtown</i>
<i>by the Great One,</i>

36:19.777 --> 36:23.144
<i>like a schoolboy</i>
<i>who had done something wrong,</i>

36:23.247 --> 36:25.272
It's not a big production.

36:25.616 --> 36:27.641
<i>Rigoletto,</i> down and dirty.

36:28.553 --> 36:30.851
Small orchestra, rented scenery.

36:31.556 --> 36:33.285
But if it goes bad,

36:33.658 --> 36:37.321
the newspapers will call it
"the shit Tetrocini <i>Rigoletto,''</i>

36:39.063 --> 36:41.588
It won't be a shit <i>Rigoletto,</i>

36:42.099 --> 36:47.059
Alfie, why don't you just conduct
under another name?

36:48.706 --> 36:50.936
You want me to change my name?

36:52.376 --> 36:53.673
Thank you.

36:56.347 --> 36:57.405
Yes.

37:00.418 --> 37:03.148
I had the Tetrocini name before you did.

37:21.405 --> 37:22.531
Carlo?

37:34.518 --> 37:35.576
Shit!

37:57.174 --> 37:59.972
What are you doing, Bennie, sitting there?

38:01.012 --> 38:02.877
Yeah, I'm just sitting.

38:03.781 --> 38:05.248
Just sitting?

38:05.916 --> 38:07.349
Just sitting.

38:41.986 --> 38:43.317
That's her name, Problema.

38:43.421 --> 38:44.649
Oh, really?
Yeah.

38:58.936 --> 39:00.733
Hello. Hello.

39:02.073 --> 39:03.631
Happy birthday, Bennie.

39:03.741 --> 39:06.073
I bet you always wanted a puppy.

39:11.716 --> 39:16.619
The Tetrocini family came to this country
in the year 1901.

39:17.588 --> 39:21.388
The first Benjamin made it big
in the wholesale chicken business.

39:21.492 --> 39:24.757
But he liked to sing,
and he played mandolin.

39:35.806 --> 39:38.673
Mr. Shakespeare, what is free verse?

39:40.878 --> 39:43.073
Something that doesn't rhyme.

39:44.281 --> 39:48.479
What else?
Has no fixed number of syllables.

39:51.522 --> 39:55.549
You know, everything that I love or that
I'm interested in, I picked up from you.

39:55.659 --> 39:59.686
You were the one who took me everywhere
and showed me books

39:59.797 --> 40:03.733
and those strange movies, <i>The Red Shoes,</i>

40:05.436 --> 40:07.631
You thought <i>Red Shoeswas</i> strange?
Yeah.

40:07.738 --> 40:10.832
What about <i>Tales of Hoffman?</i>
<i>Coppélia,</i> the dancing doll?

40:10.941 --> 40:12.806
Yeah, <i>Tales of Hoffman,</i> That...

40:12.910 --> 40:15.708
<i>Tales of Hoffman</i> always reminds me of you.

41:28.085 --> 41:30.485
Love. What is love?

41:31.489 --> 41:33.389
Love is nothing.

42:07.591 --> 42:08.580
She is my niece.

42:08.692 --> 42:09.659
Hi.
Hi.

42:09.760 --> 42:11.387
Maria Luisa...
Maria Luisa.

42:11.495 --> 42:13.053
...is 18 years old, like you.

42:16.033 --> 42:17.762
Bennie...
Does she take after you?

42:20.838 --> 42:22.829
Maria Luisa, Maria Luisa!

42:23.574 --> 42:24.734
Oh, no, no, no.

42:24.842 --> 42:27.276
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Oh, yeah.

42:27.578 --> 42:28.840
Oh, yeah.

43:02.546 --> 43:04.070
Happy birthday.

43:12.323 --> 43:13.290
Joy! Joy!

43:14.158 --> 43:16.422
Waitress, waitress. More champagne.

43:25.936 --> 43:27.096
Happy birthday, Bennie.

43:28.138 --> 43:29.105
All right.

43:44.888 --> 43:47.448
I wrote a song with that name once.
Really?

43:47.558 --> 43:50.220
You know why he's in such a jolly mood?

43:50.394 --> 43:51.452
I don't really know.

43:54.164 --> 43:55.153
It's <i>La Cucaracha,</i>

43:55.265 --> 43:58.666
Because my boat's leaving, with me on it.

43:58.936 --> 44:03.270
No! No, no, no, he's excited
because tomorrow he runs the lights.

44:04.575 --> 44:08.102
He loves to do that.
He becomes the Phantom of the Opera!

46:45.969 --> 46:47.095
Oh, God!

47:14.865 --> 47:15.923
All right, all right, all right.

48:32.376 --> 48:33.707
Come on, come on!

48:53.964 --> 48:55.124
Abelardo.

49:17.821 --> 49:18.788
Who is that?

49:54.491 --> 49:56.686
But let the play continue.

50:27.457 --> 50:28.424
Who is that?

50:28.525 --> 50:32.120
That is the most important critic and writer
in South America.

50:32.329 --> 50:37.562
She uses the pen name "Alone."
Runs the Patagonia Festival, you know.

50:44.074 --> 50:49.444
She was your brother's
teacher and mentor, until...

50:50.781 --> 50:52.112
Until what?

50:52.516 --> 50:57.146
Until she turned against him, you know.
There are many different stories why.

50:58.321 --> 51:00.221
No one knows the truth.

51:01.391 --> 51:02.881
It's a mystery.

51:06.863 --> 51:11.129
Like the mystery of your father,
and who he really is.

51:25.849 --> 51:28.943
"Carlo Tetrocini comes
from Genovese ancestors

51:29.052 --> 51:32.988
"who emigrated to Argentina in 1901.

51:35.358 --> 51:39.055
"He was discovered
by Austrian conductor Erich Kleiber,

51:39.162 --> 51:41.130
"who took him to Berlin.

51:42.065 --> 51:46.434
"He is one of the world's
great symphony conductors."

51:52.876 --> 51:55.310
Carlo Tetrocini is Tetro's father?

51:57.914 --> 51:59.677
That's our last name.

52:06.690 --> 52:11.184
"Tetrocini has conducted the Metropolitan
Philharmonic Orchestra of New York

52:11.294 --> 52:12.921
"for 35 years."

52:14.931 --> 52:17.092
How did that get in our home?

52:18.001 --> 52:20.128
How did this get in my home?

52:33.683 --> 52:34.672
Remember?

52:37.854 --> 52:42.018
But you said money was always a problem,
even made you do robberies!

52:42.125 --> 52:43.888
Money was a problem.

52:44.361 --> 52:46.989
He had money. I didn't. Okay?

52:47.097 --> 52:48.564
Let's read on.

52:48.899 --> 52:52.767
"His wife,
the acclaimed soprano Angela Panzara,

52:52.869 --> 52:55.997
"was tragically killed
in an automobile accident.

52:57.007 --> 53:00.408
"He remarried several times."
